      "userJourney": "1) The resident already holds a mobile driver's license (mDL) issued by the DMV in a supported wallet.\r\n2) They open a government online service and choose to log in with their driver's license.\r\n3) The service (relying party) requests an mDL presentation over an ISO/IEC 18013-5 mdoc flow.\r\n4) The wallet shows exactly which attributes are requested; the resident approves.\r\n5) The relying party verifies the presentation and signs the resident in, without a password and without collecting more data than needed.",
